    "narrative": "Today\u2019s primary objective for LawDog is anchored by the elite 81.53 projection for **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a soft matchup against Aaron Civale. While **Tyler Freeman** (65.77) and **Jonathan Aranda** (65.18) provide strong supporting production, **Tyler Freeman** is our standout value play; despite facing a high-caliber arm in Spencer Strider, the massive park-factor boost and his solid hitting slot elevate him to a \"Strong\" start tier. We are aggressively hunting stolen base opportunities, which explains why **Geraldo Perdomo** (64.30) remains a lock in the lineup; the combination of a favorable wind and an advantageous matchup against Boyd makes him a primary engine for both speed and run production today.\n\nManaging the bench remains a delicate balancing act, as **Wenceel Perez** (46.58) fell just short of the starting rotation. While the optimizer appreciated the potential for stolen bases against Jack Leiter given Leiter\u2019s slow delivery, **Wenceel Perez** was ultimately held out due to a bottom-of-the-order assignment that suppresses his counting stat ceiling compared to the middle-of-the-pack efficiency of **Masyn Winn** (47.61). We are also exercising caution with **Cal Raleigh**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Taylor Ward**, **Gavin Sheets**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, and **Tyler Freeman**, all of whom are currently listed under \"Lineup Pending.\" If these players are shifted down the order or benched by their respective clubs, those efficiency scores will collapse. **Daulton Varsho** and **Bryson Stott** provide reliable depth, but we will monitor the weather reports throughout the morning to ensure no late-breaking warnings impact their high-efficiency projections against their respective opponents.",
